cos^nx
\cos^{2}(x)=\frac{1+\cos(2x)}{2}
\cos(x)\cos(y)=\frac{1}{2}\big(\cos(x-y)-\cos(x+y)\big)
u = e^{ix}
v=e^{-ix}
u v = 1
v=1/u
\cos x=(u+v)/2
\cos^4 x = 1/16 (u+v)^4 = 1/16(u^4 + 4 u^3 v + 6 u^2 v^2 + 4 u v^3 + v^4) \\ =1/16 (u^4 + u^2 + 6 + v^2 + v^4)
 2 \cos 4x = (u^4 + v^4) \\ 2  \cos2x = (u^2 + v^2)   
 \cos^4 x= 1/16 (2 \cos 4x +8 \cos 2x + 6)
